<TITLE> Tigers put WI in a spin </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 17 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh's three spinners left West Indies in tatters at tea on the first day of the second and final Test at St George's, Gernada on Friday. The trio of Mahmudullah Riyad, Shakib Al Hasan and Enamul Haque Jr shared seven wickets to leave the home side, put into bat, on 178-7. Off-spinner Mahmudullah led the way with 3-27 while stand-in skipper Shakib and slow left-arm bowler Enamul, playing in place of the injured regular captain Mashrafe Bin Mortaza, snared two each. The home side, missing the bulk of their first-choice players owing to a contractual and pay dispute with West Indies board (WICB), slumped from 107-3 at lunch losing four more wickets when play resumed after a lengthy rain delay. Travis Dowlin was batting on 59 off 104 balls and Ryan Austin 2 respectively at the break. Bangladesh won the first Test in St Vincent by 95 runs on Jul
